			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello, 
<br />

<br />
Here is my my problem:  
<br />
I've been using textual confirmation for 2 weeks and it's been doing great. I used to go by basic subsilver. 
<br />
Only, I added recently a new template (ashfuel  <a href="http://demo.forumshotel.org/demo/index.php?s=80&amp;mforum=demo" target="_blank">http://demo.forumshotel.org/demo/index.php?s=80&amp;mforum=demo</a>
<br />
), and since then, the Textual confirmation question has disappeared from the registration form, and all users trying to register are rejected for &quot;failing to answer the TC Q&quot;!!! <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="Crying or Very sad" border="0" /> 
<br />
What  can I do to fix it?
<br />

<br />
thank you!  
<br />
(I know that I've just asked this question to the author of TC, sorry.)
<br />
PS: I've installed textual confirmation with Easymod</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
