		<td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%"><span class="postdetails">Posted: Wed Jan 10, 2007 4:18 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
				<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap">&nbsp;</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">added recently a new template ... and since then, the Textual confirmation question has disappeared from the registration form ...
<br />
What can I do to fix it?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
A bit of manual work is required.
<br />

<br />
1) Copy the file &quot;<span style="font-weight: bold">templates/subSilver/admin/textual_confirmation.tpl</span>&quot; to the file &quot;<span style="font-weight: bold">templates/<span style="font-style: italic">your_template_name</span>/admin/textual_confirmation.tpl</span>&quot;.
<br />

<br />
2) In the new template, find the file &quot;<span style="font-weight: bold">templates/<span style="font-style: italic">your_template_name</span>/profile_add_body.tpl</span>&quot;.
<br />

<br />
Edit the file: find the string
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">&lt;!-- END switch_confirm --&gt;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
and after the string, add the following:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;!-- BEGIN switch_textual_confirm --&gt;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;tr&gt; 
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;td class=&quot;row1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gen&quot;&gt;&#123;TEXTUAL_CONFIRMATION_QUESTION&#125; * &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gensmall&quot;&gt;&#123;L_TEXTUAL_CONFIRMATION_EXPLAIN&#125;&lt;/td&gt;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;td class=&quot;row2&quot;&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; class=&quot;post&quot; style=&quot;width&#58; 200px&quot; name=&quot;tc_answer&quot; size=&quot;25&quot; value=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;/tr&gt;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;!-- END switch_textual_confirm --&gt;
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Then check that TC works well in the both cases:
<br />
* when an user successfully answers a qeustions, and
<br />
* when a bot fails to answer.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I know that I've just asked this question to the author of TC.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
This forum is exactly the place to ask the author of TC, so you are right.<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
